    "passives": {
      "IamtheQueenPassiveAVictoriaRegularBoss": {
        "id": "IamtheQueenPassiveAVictoriaRegularBoss",
        "found": true,
        "localization": {
          "name": "Étoile Queen",
          "description": "This unit cannot fall asleep or be sent to the reinforcements from the battlefield.\n\nThis unit's attacks will not wake sleeping enemies, and heal this unit for 1% of total damage dealt.\n\nWhenever another ally takes damage from an attack, this unit will have its TU reduced to 0. Then this effect cannot trigger again until 50TU advances. Effects that influence TU order may interrupt the extra turn (e.g. Stuns targeting the lowest TU target).\n\nIf this unit has another ally on the battlefield, whenever this unit takes damage from an attack and survives until after the end of the turn, this unit grants a random enemy the Deep Sleep status effect for 100TU, even if they have already slept while on the battlefield. This is not a Skin passive skill.\n\nDeep Sleep will overwrite other status effects, cannot be overwritten by Burn or Sleep status effects, and cannot be Purified."
        }
      },
      "WarQueenPassiveAVictoriaRegularBoss": {
        "id": "WarQueenPassiveAVictoriaRegularBoss",
        "found": true,
        "localization": {
          "name": "Étoile's Grace",
          "description": "This unit enters battle with a Power Charge. This unit has 50% damage reduction from attacks for 100TU.\n\nIf this unit would be defeated while it has a Power Charge, it instead survives with 1 HP and then cannot be defeated until its next turn. The Power Charge will be consumed when this effect is triggered.\n\nEach time an ally (including this unit) gets the turn, this unit will become Purified (negative status effects like sleep, burn or poison are removed) at the end of that turn.\n\nEach time an enemy gets the turn, this unit will become Enraged at the end of that turn. An Enraged unit's attack is increased to 1.5x until the end of their next turn. Enrage will overwrite any existing Weak or Enrage effects on this unit.\n\nPower Charges can be consumed by certain skills to activate or enhance their effects. Power Charges will be removed if this unit leaves the battlefield. Power Charges cannot stack."
        }
      }
